1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:02,369
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

2
00:00:03,269 --> 00:00:04,537
[GRUNTS AND CHUCKLES]

3
00:00:08,274 --> 00:00:09,309
[CHUCKLING]

4
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:34,401
[GRUNTING]

5
00:00:43,576 --> 00:00:46,679
Why? One of the kids
stuck some stuff.

6
00:00:47,614 --> 00:00:49,516
[GRUNTING]

7
00:00:52,452 --> 00:00:55,388
We are now approaching
the cookie section.

8
00:00:55,422 --> 00:00:57,624
Would anybody like to select
some cookies?

9
00:00:59,926 --> 00:01:01,761
[GRUNTING]

10
00:01:06,666 --> 00:01:11,271
"...chemically
separated chicken.

11
00:01:12,305 --> 00:01:14,674
"Modified wheat flour.

12
00:01:14,707 --> 00:01:18,845
"Twice as sodium erythorbate.

13
00:01:18,878 --> 00:01:22,348
"Sodium nitrate." Tempting.
No, thanks.

14
00:01:23,683 --> 00:01:25,685
Let's find something to eat.

15
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:43,536
Xanthan gum.

16
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:47,240
Sorbic acid,
sodium benzoate,
calca...

17
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:49,742
David, this is not for you.
This will give you
brain damage.

18
00:01:54,414 --> 00:01:56,616
Stop staring, you're not
so pretty yourself.

19
00:02:08,595 --> 00:02:10,396
Hi, David.
[CHUCKLES]

20
00:02:20,773 --> 00:02:23,209
[DAVID GRUNTING]

21
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:34,521
SALLY: Hold the door. Hold it.
Oh, yeah. All right, get
the door open and let me in.

22
00:02:43,796 --> 00:02:47,333
SALLY:
Yes! Home sweet home.

23
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:50,270
Take off the shoes,
turn on the TV.

24
00:02:50,303 --> 00:02:54,774
And yes, ladies and gentleman,
it is another scintillating
afternoon at the Goodson home.

25
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:57,977
All right.

26
00:02:58,011 --> 00:03:00,947
For our matinee today
we are pleased

27
00:03:01,881 --> 00:03:03,850
to present
The Wizard of Oz.

28
00:03:03,883 --> 00:03:06,653
"Yes, isn't that the movie
you've only seen
like 30,000 times?"

29
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:08,221
Yes, but,

30
00:03:08,254 --> 00:03:13,693
it is starring Judy Garland,
Frank Morgan, Ray Bolger,
Bert Lahr and Jack Haley.

31
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:16,729
Approximate screening time,
one hour forty-one minutes.

32
00:03:16,763 --> 00:03:18,731
Copyright Loew's Incorporated.

33
00:03:19,532 --> 00:03:20,833
Enjoy.

34
00:03:22,535 --> 00:03:23,970
What do you want
for lunch, sweetie?

35
00:03:24,771 --> 00:03:26,272
Huh?

36
00:03:26,306 --> 00:03:27,740
All right, here are your
choices.

37
00:03:27,774 --> 00:03:29,943
I have, I have...

38
00:03:30,643 --> 00:03:32,345
Lasagna?

39
00:03:32,378 --> 00:03:34,647
And I have cabbage rolls.

40
00:03:34,681 --> 00:03:37,283
Lasagna, cabbage?
Cabbage, lasagna?
Cab... cab...

41
00:03:37,317 --> 00:03:39,085
Which one do you want?

42
00:03:39,118 --> 00:03:42,021
May I suggest the cabbage roll,
because tonight we are having
spaghetti and meat balls.

43
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:43,890
Which do you want?
Come on.

44
00:03:43,923 --> 00:03:46,459
Cabbage rolls!
Good choice, honey.

45
00:03:47,594 --> 00:03:49,796
This is living.

46
00:03:50,997 --> 00:03:52,565
Hmm.
[GRUNTING]

47
00:03:55,368 --> 00:03:57,370
Mrs. Goodson?

48
00:03:57,403 --> 00:03:58,738
Somebody here for you.

49
00:04:01,341 --> 00:04:03,810
Mrs. Goodson?
SALLY:Yeah.

50
00:04:03,843 --> 00:04:06,779
This is Gladys Johnson of
The Department of Child Welfare.

51
00:04:06,813 --> 00:04:08,514
Who did you say
you were looking for?

52
00:04:08,548 --> 00:04:09,749
Mrs. Goodson?

53
00:04:09,782 --> 00:04:11,551
Mrs. Sally Goodson.

54
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:14,020
Mrs. Goodson isn't in,
this is the maid.

55
00:04:14,053 --> 00:04:16,789
Mrs. Goodson, it is urgent
that we speak.

56
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:19,792
I said this is the maid
and I got to go clean
or I'm gonna get fired.

57
00:04:22,729 --> 00:04:26,432
The wolves are
nipping at your heels,
honey bunch.

58
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:28,801
Don't worry.
I won't let them
get their hands on you.

59
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:36,542
Hi, Sid.
Is my sister home?

60
00:04:36,576 --> 00:04:39,112
I don't know.
She just said
she was the maid.

61
00:04:39,145 --> 00:04:41,481
Oh! Delusions
of grandeur, huh?

62
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,726
David, use the spoon.

63
00:04:58,097 --> 00:04:59,999
[GRUNTS]
David, use the spoon.

64
00:05:02,502 --> 00:05:04,370
[SIGHS]

65
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:06,973
I'm not playing
Miracle Worker
here, David.

66
00:05:07,006 --> 00:05:08,608
Use the spoon.

67
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:11,778
[LAUGHING]

68
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:13,913
Use the spoon, David.

69
00:05:13,946 --> 00:05:16,482
Love of my life,
use the spoon.

70
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:19,619
Hello! David!

71
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:20,920
Use the spoon.

72
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:23,890
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

73
00:05:23,923 --> 00:05:25,625
BEA: Open up.
I know you're in there.

74
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,427
Oh, great!

75
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:34,167
David, Aunty Bea has come
to call. What a treat!

76
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,835
[INCREASES TV VOLUME]

77
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:40,540
Sorry, I didn't hear
the bell.

78
00:05:40,573 --> 00:05:42,642
Yeah, right.

79
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:46,412
I would think that you would
welcome someone to talk to.

80
00:05:46,446 --> 00:05:48,715
I have someone
to talk to.

81
00:05:48,748 --> 00:05:51,417
David and I were
just discussing cutlery.

82
00:05:51,451 --> 00:05:54,620
So I heard.
So did everyone else
on the floor.

83
00:05:54,654 --> 00:05:56,856
[KISSES]
Everyone except David.

84
00:05:56,889 --> 00:05:59,092
Okay. Sit down.
I wanna talk to you.

85
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:01,427
Who's dead?
Abraham Lincoln. Sit down

86
00:06:03,229 --> 00:06:05,998
All right,
you are drinking wine
in the afternoon now.

87
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:07,867
It's leftover from
the Academy Awards.

88
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:10,002
I had a party.

89
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:12,772
I bet that's the last time
you cleaned this place. Oh,
why doesn't that surprise me?

90
00:06:12,805 --> 00:06:14,607
Go home.
Eat off your floor.

91
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,008
What are you doing
here anyway?

92
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:19,479
I was at the dentist.
And I thought I come by
in person,

93
00:06:19,512 --> 00:06:21,481
and make you promise me
something.

94
00:06:21,514 --> 00:06:23,516
What? I shudder to ask.

95
00:06:23,549 --> 00:06:25,852
Promise me that you'll have
lunch with me on Sunday.

96
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:28,154
[TSKS] You and who else?

97
00:06:28,187 --> 00:06:29,822
He's very charming.
I'm sure.

98
00:06:29,856 --> 00:06:31,657
And he's on his 40's.

99
00:06:31,691 --> 00:06:33,025
Don't fix me up
anymore.

100
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:35,561
Recently widowed,
has no children.

101
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:37,096
[SIGHS]
Sounds really hot.

102
00:06:37,663 --> 00:06:39,232
Look. Look.

103
00:06:39,265 --> 00:06:41,467
Just do me a favor.
He's lonely.

104
00:06:41,501 --> 00:06:44,170
Oh, so now what are you
doing? Setting up the 100
neediest cases?

105
00:06:44,203 --> 00:06:46,806
I told him all about you
and David. He'd love
to meet you.

106
00:06:46,839 --> 00:06:48,608
Uh-uh. I can't do it.

107
00:06:48,641 --> 00:06:49,876
I'm busy on Sunday.

108
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,010
Doing what?

109
00:06:51,043 --> 00:06:52,812
Dancing
Swan Lake,
that's what.

110
00:06:52,845 --> 00:06:54,046
Sally, just do it.

111
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,848
I mean, you owe me this.

112
00:06:55,882 --> 00:06:58,017
Can he come?
No, he cannot come.

113
00:06:58,050 --> 00:07:00,086
This is for adults only,
except for you.

114
00:07:00,119 --> 00:07:02,188
God, you turning
into a recluse,
you know that?

115
00:07:02,221 --> 00:07:04,157
Thank you very much. [SIGHS]

116
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,792
Okay, honey,
your cousin Justine

117
00:07:05,825 --> 00:07:08,594
is gonna come over on Sunday
and spend the day with you.

118
00:07:08,628 --> 00:07:11,764
You like that? Now, why
don't you just eat it
with a spoon, right there.

119
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:13,666
[SCREAMS]
Ah! What did I do?

120
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:18,671
Only the right hand can put
food in the mouth.

121
00:07:18,704 --> 00:07:20,106
Don't you know anything? Why?

122
00:07:20,139 --> 00:07:22,809
I don't know, it's a little
secret between David and God.

123
00:07:22,842 --> 00:07:25,678
All right, I'll see you
on Sunday.

124
00:07:25,711 --> 00:07:28,881
And if you please, wear
something that doesn't have
dried food all over it.

125
00:07:28,915 --> 00:07:31,250
Yes, go. Give me time
to scrape a dress.

126
00:07:31,984 --> 00:07:33,252
Walk me to the elevator.

127
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:34,954
[SCOFFS]

128
00:07:34,987 --> 00:07:37,190
Like you're six-years-old
and you can't
get there yourself.

129
00:07:37,223 --> 00:07:39,492
[SCOFFS]
You need a babysitter.

130
00:07:41,894 --> 00:07:43,196
I got a letter
from Susan.

131
00:07:43,896 --> 00:07:45,665
Susan who?

132
00:07:45,698 --> 00:07:47,834
Susan, your daughter Susan.

133
00:07:48,835 --> 00:07:50,570
She's pregnant.

134
00:07:50,603 --> 00:07:52,605
[SIGHS] What?

135
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:54,607
[SCOFFS] She's only 18.

136
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:55,942
She's 19.

137
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:57,076
Already?

138
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:01,547
Did she happen to mention
whether or not she's married?

139
00:08:01,581 --> 00:08:03,082
She's getting married
in a few weeks.

140
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:04,750
I like that.
First things first.

141
00:08:06,752 --> 00:08:08,154
Why don't you call her?

142
00:08:08,187 --> 00:08:10,656
Nah. I call her,
she'll probably miscarry.

143
00:08:11,624 --> 00:08:13,292
[SIGHS]

144
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:17,296
We haven't been so close
and she chose to move
3,000 miles away from me.

145
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:18,798
You should go
to the wedding.

146
00:08:20,266 --> 00:08:22,602
I don't have the wardrobe.
Well, buy the wardrobe.

147
00:08:22,635 --> 00:08:24,770
Yeah. Freelance editors
make that kind of money.

148
00:08:24,804 --> 00:08:26,005
I'll give you the money.

149
00:08:26,038 --> 00:08:27,807
No, you will not give me
the money.

150
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,208
It would be my pleasure.

151
00:08:29,242 --> 00:08:31,844
It was your pleasure
to buy us a VCR.

152
00:08:31,878 --> 00:08:34,847
You know, I don't like you
that much to
make you that happy.

153
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:35,982
[ELEVATOR DOOR OPENS]

154
00:08:38,918 --> 00:08:41,354
But don't worry about those
hemorrhoids, they'll go away.

155
00:08:41,387 --> 00:08:42,989
The itching will stop.

156
00:08:49,395 --> 00:08:50,730
[SIGHS]

157
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:53,232
[DOOR CLOSES]

158
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:55,067
[GRUNTING] David.

159
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:57,136
Did you hear that?

160
00:08:59,839 --> 00:09:01,173
Your sister's pregnant.

161
00:09:03,309 --> 00:09:04,810
And getting married.

162
00:09:06,145 --> 00:09:07,680
In 19.
[GASPS]

163
00:09:09,348 --> 00:09:11,851
I think you and I are
a little bit
out of touch, buddy.

164
00:09:12,952 --> 00:09:14,787
[GROANING]

165
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:17,189
Don't be upset that you
weren't invited
to the wedding.

166
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:20,026
She didn't
invite me either.

167
00:09:21,694 --> 00:09:22,995
But maybe that's better.

168
00:09:23,029 --> 00:09:24,964
You know
that person's gonna
show up.

169
00:09:24,997 --> 00:09:26,699
[SNORTS]
Remember him?

170
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:29,769
He used to be your father.

171
00:09:34,941 --> 00:09:37,610
But, you know what?
It wouldn't have killed her
to invite us.

172
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:40,980
I used to be her mother.

173
00:09:43,182 --> 00:09:44,917
SUSAN:
I don't wanna
talk about it.

174
00:09:44,951 --> 00:09:47,053
PHILIP:
Come on, Susan,
you were fine.

175
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:48,854
Everybody forgets lines.

176
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:50,323
Daddy, will you stop?

177
00:09:50,356 --> 00:09:52,058
Will you forget
the damn play!

178
00:09:52,091 --> 00:09:53,826
Susan, watch your mouth.

179
00:09:54,226 --> 00:09:55,728
What happened?

180
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:58,764
PHILIP: She's upset.

181
00:09:58,798 --> 00:10:00,366
She forgot a few lines
in the play.

182
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:02,168
SALLY:
Honey, Shakespeare,
who knew?

183
00:10:02,201 --> 00:10:04,737
I bet everybody thought it was
supposed to be that way.

184
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:06,872
How would you know?
You weren't there.

185
00:10:06,906 --> 00:10:10,343
Sweetheart, the babysitter
canceled at the last minute.
What was I supposed to do?

186
00:10:10,376 --> 00:10:12,078
[SCOFFS]

187
00:10:12,111 --> 00:10:14,046
Get a different babysitter.

188
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,082
Sweetheart, David doesn't
like strangers.

189
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:17,283
Oh! Oh! Oh!

190
00:10:20,086 --> 00:10:22,722
For once
he could have adjusted.
Wouldn't have killed him.

191
00:10:22,755 --> 00:10:24,824
Well, it didn't
kill her either.

192
00:10:39,205 --> 00:10:42,308
You know, if you weren't
in here sulking,

193
00:10:42,341 --> 00:10:44,944
you could come out here
and have some
terrific brownies.

194
00:10:49,515 --> 00:10:51,150
Sweetie...

195
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:56,355
this is Junior high school,
the critics weren't there.

196
00:10:56,389 --> 00:10:57,857
Neither were you.

197
00:11:00,026 --> 00:11:02,261
You can be a real beast
sometimes, you know that?

198
00:11:02,762 --> 00:11:04,096
Yeah?

199
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:05,965
I hate you, too.

200
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:07,433
You don't hate me,

201
00:11:08,234 --> 00:11:09,969
I'm your mother.

202
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,804
You may resent me,

203
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:14,740
and you may be filled
with ambivalence,

204
00:11:14,774 --> 00:11:18,144
offended,
and indignant as hell,
but trust me,

205
00:11:18,177 --> 00:11:20,746
daughters don't hate
their mothers.

206
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:22,848
Except in my case,
that's different.

207
00:11:26,852 --> 00:11:28,287
Why not we just...

208
00:11:30,322 --> 00:11:32,258
cut the crap and you give me
a big old kiss.

209
00:11:32,892 --> 00:11:35,461
Huh? [LAUGHING]

210
00:11:35,494 --> 00:11:38,764
[SIGHS] So what if we weren't
invited to the wedding.

211
00:11:38,798 --> 00:11:40,366
[TSKS] To hell with it.

212
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:45,404
I've got an idea.

213
00:11:45,438 --> 00:11:49,742
Why don't you come in my room
with me and help me pick out
a dress for my blind date?

214
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,813
Please, God, he'll be blind.

215
00:11:53,846 --> 00:11:56,182
Oh, man. Oh, man. Oh, man.
Oh, here's one.
This is good.

216
00:11:57,349 --> 00:11:58,751
How is this?

217
00:12:00,486 --> 00:12:04,190
What? What?
Don't give me that look.

218
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:06,525
You think I look like
a prison matron in this,
don't you?

219
00:12:09,261 --> 00:12:11,997
[SCOFFS] You're right. I do.
You're always right.

220
00:12:12,598 --> 00:12:15,768
Oh, now here's one. This.

221
00:12:18,604 --> 00:12:21,240
It's a little acrylic creation.

222
00:12:21,273 --> 00:12:25,878
Sally Goodson, equally at home
yachting the afternoon away,

223
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:30,015
or in the frozen
produce department
of her neighborhood A&P.

224
00:12:34,153 --> 00:12:36,489
Honey?

225
00:12:36,522 --> 00:12:40,960
All right. Tomorrow you and I
will go out shopping and buy
me a new dress.

226
00:12:43,395 --> 00:12:45,264
[HORN TOOTING]

227
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:58,210
Mrs. Goodson?
Yes.

228
00:12:58,244 --> 00:13:00,913
I am Gladys Johnson from
The Department
of Child Welfare.

229
00:13:02,982 --> 00:13:04,950
Please don't make me
file a report on you.

230
00:13:08,053 --> 00:13:10,556
Can we go somewhere
and talk?

231
00:13:10,589 --> 00:13:13,192
If I buy you a cup of coffee,
is that considered a bribe?

232
00:13:14,226 --> 00:13:15,895
I'll buy you one.

233
00:13:15,928 --> 00:13:17,563
Got an expense account
up to a dollar.

234
00:13:20,132 --> 00:13:21,567
Let's go, David.

235
00:13:22,935 --> 00:13:24,170
I sent you two letters.

236
00:13:25,571 --> 00:13:27,606
Damn, that post office.

237
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,075
Slipped the last one
under your door.

238
00:13:30,109 --> 00:13:32,611
Yeah, it's probably
still there with the rest
of the debris.

239
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:35,481
In it I explained
the department
is taking a new census

240
00:13:35,514 --> 00:13:37,883
of handicapped children
in the Tri-state area.

241
00:13:37,917 --> 00:13:41,487
Now, when computers
in Connecticut were put online,
a discrepancy was noticed.

242
00:13:42,087 --> 00:13:43,289
Yeah? What?

243
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:45,558
New York has David assigned
to a facility in Connecticut,

244
00:13:45,591 --> 00:13:47,560
but Connecticut never heard
of him.

245
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:50,029
Well, that is a discrepancy,
isn't it?

246
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:52,865
You jerking
me around, lady?

247
00:13:53,299 --> 00:13:54,466
I'm trying.

