been lately?

497
00:26:27,819 --> 00:26:28,954
Where have I been?

498
00:26:29,788 --> 00:26:31,389
Right here.

499
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:34,125
Try to look in at someone
besides your son
once in a while.

500
00:26:34,726 --> 00:26:36,094
My son?

501
00:26:36,127 --> 00:26:38,663
Wow, I guess that says it all,
doesn't it?

502
00:26:38,697 --> 00:26:39,931
That's not what I meant.

503
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,101
I do the best I can.

504
00:26:47,339 --> 00:26:49,441
Prove it.

505
00:26:49,474 --> 00:26:52,010
What do you mean?
How am I supposed
to do that?

506
00:26:52,043 --> 00:26:54,779
Leave the kids with Bea
for a weekend,
let's get out of here.

507
00:26:56,081 --> 00:26:58,283
You know that I cannot
leave David.

508
00:27:00,819 --> 00:27:01,886
Well...

509
00:27:04,089 --> 00:27:05,824
That says it all,
doesn't it?

510
00:27:13,398 --> 00:27:15,734
Getting it somewhere else?

511
00:27:15,767 --> 00:27:17,402
No, I'm not getting it
somewhere else.

512
00:27:18,803 --> 00:27:19,871
I'm not getting it.

513
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:22,307
And you know what?

514
00:27:22,340 --> 00:27:23,708
I don't miss it.

515
00:27:24,309 --> 00:27:26,444
You know what I miss?

516
00:27:26,478 --> 00:27:30,782
I miss coming home
and arguing about politics,
and how much money you spend.

517
00:27:30,815 --> 00:27:33,251
I miss new recipes

518
00:27:33,284 --> 00:27:36,321
and watching my daughter
get giddy over nothing.

519
00:27:37,856 --> 00:27:40,392
I miss laughter.
That's what I miss,
not sex.

520
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:50,468
I'm sorry.

521
00:27:52,237 --> 00:27:53,471
Sure, you're
always sorry.

522
00:27:56,007 --> 00:28:00,111
Well, I'm sorry because
I always do something
to be sorry for.

523
00:28:02,213 --> 00:28:03,948
Ask Bea,
I was a rotten kid.

524
00:28:05,984 --> 00:28:07,085
Now, I'm a rotten grownup.

525
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:11,756
I love you.

526
00:28:13,491 --> 00:28:14,993
I even love your nose.

527
00:28:16,394 --> 00:28:17,829
[LAUGHS]

528
00:28:21,099 --> 00:28:22,333
Someday...

529
00:28:23,201 --> 00:28:24,469
Someday...

530
00:28:24,502 --> 00:28:26,504
Someday what?
Someday nothing.

531
00:28:28,239 --> 00:28:30,075
You love me too much
to ever leave me.

532
00:28:33,211 --> 00:28:35,447
You are here
for the duration.

533
00:28:44,022 --> 00:28:45,223
JOHN: You look nice.

534
00:28:46,925 --> 00:28:48,460
Yeah? Well, this is it.
This is...

535
00:28:50,261 --> 00:28:52,497
my wardrobe.

536
00:28:52,530 --> 00:28:56,301
'Cause if you ask me out again,
you gonna have to take me to
someplace I can go naked.

537
00:28:57,235 --> 00:28:58,903
[SIGHS]

538
00:28:58,937 --> 00:29:00,505
Surprised you asked me out
this time.

539
00:29:00,538 --> 00:29:02,107
Why?

540
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:03,508
Because you got
a load of David.

541
00:29:05,043 --> 00:29:08,813
Look, if my candor
approaches rudeness,

542
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:10,248
you're gonna
have to forgive me.

543
00:29:11,950 --> 00:29:14,185
I don't like it when people
freak out over my kid.

544
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:23,361
Yeah. Well, you know, maybe
this was not such a hot idea.

545
00:29:23,394 --> 00:29:24,896
Oh, please stay.

546
00:29:25,630 --> 00:29:26,998
It wasn't David.

547
00:29:27,432 --> 00:29:28,500
Yeah, right.

548
00:29:29,467 --> 00:29:31,069
All right.

549
00:29:31,102 --> 00:29:33,204
I wasn't really prepared
for him, I guess.

550
00:29:34,572 --> 00:29:37,242
He did stop me in my tracks.
But it was...

551
00:29:40,178 --> 00:29:41,312
It was something you did.

552
00:29:42,213 --> 00:29:43,248
It... What?

553
00:29:45,316 --> 00:29:47,051
You made fun of him.

554
00:29:47,085 --> 00:29:49,154
Well, at least I thought
you did.

555
00:29:49,187 --> 00:29:51,022
But, then...

556
00:29:51,055 --> 00:29:54,259
I spoke to Bea and she said
that sometimes

557
00:29:54,292 --> 00:29:56,127
when you sound like
you're being cruel,

558
00:29:56,161 --> 00:29:59,230
you're really just making
jokes to cover up how uptight
you feel.

559
00:30:00,932 --> 00:30:02,300
It doesn't mean anything.

560
00:30:04,969 --> 00:30:08,907
So, you discuss my so called
sense of humor with my sister
behind my back?

561
00:30:08,940 --> 00:30:10,375
Don't get mad.

562
00:30:10,408 --> 00:30:14,012
You are one presumptuous
wallpaper hanger.

563
00:30:14,045 --> 00:30:15,513
I don't hang it, I sell it.

564
00:30:17,415 --> 00:30:19,284
Except for you,
I'd give it to you.

565
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:23,488
Hand painted.
Silk screened.
Flocked.

566
00:30:24,289 --> 00:30:25,456
Am I tempting you?

567
00:30:26,357 --> 00:30:27,959
You're nauseating me.

568
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,329
Excuse me.
Are you ready
to order?

569
00:30:33,031 --> 00:30:35,233
What's the most
expensive thing
you got on the menu?

570
00:30:37,368 --> 00:30:38,570
Suffer, you.

571
00:30:39,604 --> 00:30:41,139
[SNORING]

572
00:30:45,944 --> 00:30:48,112
SALLY: Ah, please. Eh.

573
00:30:49,247 --> 00:30:51,983
Garbage, garbage, garbage.

574
00:30:53,618 --> 00:30:55,019
[SNICKERS]

575
00:30:56,487 --> 00:30:57,889
Hey, babe.

576
00:30:58,489 --> 00:31:00,124
You wanna hear some crap?

577
00:31:01,192 --> 00:31:03,127
Listen to this.

578
00:31:03,161 --> 00:31:05,463
"Montgomery left Greystone
as he had entered it.

579
00:31:06,397 --> 00:31:08,032
"Penniless.

580
00:31:08,066 --> 00:31:11,636
"Save for his silken
waistcoats and
golden fobs.

581
00:31:11,669 --> 00:31:15,206
"Upstairs Melanie lay prostrate
on her bed,

582
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:19,143
"weeping scalding tears
for her profligate lover."

583
00:31:19,177 --> 00:31:21,079
[CLICKS TONGUE]

584
00:31:22,413 --> 00:31:23,648
I know how you feel, honey.

585
00:31:25,316 --> 00:31:27,252
Take it from somebody
who's been there.

586
00:31:28,519 --> 00:31:31,122
It gets easier.

587
00:31:31,155 --> 00:31:33,258
PHILIP:
I left you some money
in the top drawer.

588
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:34,993
SALLY: Do you need
your hair dryer?

589
00:31:35,026 --> 00:31:38,463
This is a separation,
you're not supposed
to help me pack.

590
00:31:38,496 --> 00:31:40,965
Sorry, I don't know
the etiquette of divorce.

591
00:31:40,999 --> 00:31:43,234
Not a divorce,
this is a separation.

592
00:32:00,485 --> 00:32:04,756
I want you to tell me the truth,
because if you don't, you won't
come back.

593
00:32:04,789 --> 00:32:07,225
It's easier to stay away
than to come back to a lie.

594
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:18,002
What do you
want to know?

595
00:32:20,571 --> 00:32:23,541
I want to know
about the woman
you're going to.

596
00:32:23,574 --> 00:32:25,109
The one who
is waiting for you.

597
00:32:28,246 --> 00:32:30,114
[ELEVATOR DOOR OPENS]

598
00:32:30,148 --> 00:32:31,316
MAN: Hey.

599
00:32:31,716 --> 00:32:33,318
Who is she?

600
00:32:33,351 --> 00:32:35,253
[ALARM BUZZING]
Just a girl at the office.

601
00:32:35,820 --> 00:32:37,455
She's nothing.

602
00:32:37,488 --> 00:32:39,023
Then why are you
going to her?

603
00:32:40,325 --> 00:32:42,060
MAN: Open the door.

604
00:32:42,093 --> 00:32:45,396
Because I don't know
where else to go.

605
00:32:45,430 --> 00:32:49,300
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]
What's going on there?
You got a problem? Open up.

606
00:32:54,372 --> 00:32:55,807
You could stay here.

607
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,642
I can't.
Why?

608
00:32:58,676 --> 00:33:00,345
I can't do it anymore.

609
00:33:00,645 --> 00:33:03,181
Do what?

610
00:33:03,214 --> 00:33:05,683
I can't face one more father
at the playground.

611
00:33:07,852 --> 00:33:10,188
I can't watch the look
on his face...

612
00:33:10,221 --> 00:33:13,524
when he looks at David,
and then his own boy.

613
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:17,295
I, I can't bear the relief
on his face.

614
00:33:17,328 --> 00:33:20,698
The pain in the eyes
of the women when David
falls down and hurts himself.

615
00:33:20,732 --> 00:33:22,300
I just can't bear it.

616
00:33:22,333 --> 00:33:23,701
And you think I can?

617
00:33:24,235 --> 00:33:26,070
Yeah.

618
00:33:26,104 --> 00:33:28,439
Yeah, I think you can.
I think you can do anything.

619
00:33:30,308 --> 00:33:31,576
Taxi.
[SIGHS]

620
00:33:33,177 --> 00:33:34,379
Wait a minute, hold up.

621
00:33:34,412 --> 00:33:36,614
Before you turn me into
some kind of saint here,

622
00:33:36,647 --> 00:33:38,049
and I lose you for good,

623
00:33:39,117 --> 00:33:41,352
I want you to
know something.

624
00:33:41,386 --> 00:33:42,787
There's not one day
that goes by

625
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:45,723
that I don't blame David
for what isn't his fault.

626
00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:47,725
Not one day that I don't...

627
00:33:47,759 --> 00:33:50,595
I don't wake up and ask myself,
"What the hell did I do
to deserve this?"

628
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:54,432
But I feed him,
and I clean him,

629
00:33:55,333 --> 00:33:56,768
and sometimes I hate him.

630
00:34:02,707 --> 00:34:07,278
I have this fantasy that
one day David is just gonna
wake up healed,

631
00:34:07,311 --> 00:34:11,249
and he's gonna tell me that
he knew all along everything
that I did for him.

632
00:34:13,451 --> 00:34:17,655
He's gonna tell me that
he knows every time
that I wiped his ass,

633
00:34:17,688 --> 00:34:20,825
and sat with him watching
some stupid movie.

634
00:34:23,227 --> 00:34:24,629
[CRYING]
That's the worst part.

635
00:34:24,662 --> 00:34:27,632
Because I need him
to thank me.

636
00:34:29,801 --> 00:34:31,369
He can't thank me.

637
00:34:33,638 --> 00:34:34,672
[SNIFFLES]

638
00:34:36,607 --> 00:34:38,709
But I do what
I have to do.

639
00:34:40,411 --> 00:34:42,814
And I want you to know that
if you come back,

640
00:34:42,847 --> 00:34:49,320
that you're coming back as
somebody who knows how hard
it is to do what you have to do.

641
00:34:49,353 --> 00:34:53,157
And who understands that
some times you, you just have
to get away and rest.

642
00:34:54,258 --> 00:34:55,827
So, I want you to go away
and rest.

643
00:34:57,795 --> 00:34:59,263
And when you're rested...

644
00:35:00,898 --> 00:35:02,400
[SNIFFLES]

645
00:35:02,433 --> 00:35:04,335
I want you to
make up your mind.

646
00:35:04,368 --> 00:35:05,837
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

647
00:35:21,853 --> 00:35:23,354
I love you.

648
00:35:27,525 --> 00:35:29,560
Of course you do.

649
00:35:37,635 --> 00:35:39,170
[SNIFFLES]

650
00:35:39,971 --> 00:35:41,439
[SIGHS]

651
00:35:43,941 --> 00:35:45,543
[TV PLAYING SOFTLY]

652
00:35:47,011 --> 00:35:48,713
[DAVID GROANING]

653
00:36:17,842 --> 00:36:20,578
[KIDS CHATTING]
[CARNIVAL MUSIC PLAYING]

654
00:36:22,547 --> 00:36:25,449
SALLY: Look. Look, David. Look.
[DAVID GRUNTING]

655
00:36:25,483 --> 00:36:26,717
Look at the carousels.

656
00:36:26,751 --> 00:36:28,286
See the horses?

657
00:36:28,319 --> 00:36:30,021
[DAVID AND SALLY LAUGHING]

658
00:36:30,054 --> 00:36:32,890
MAN: [WHISTLES] Come on.
Oh, David. Whoa. Whoa.

659
00:36:32,924 --> 00:36:35,593
Are there seat belts
on this thing?
Yeah, for sure. I...

660
00:36:35,626 --> 00:36:38,496
Hang on to him very,
very tightly, because
he doesn't have balance.

661
00:36:38,529 --> 00:36:39,564
Don't you worry.

662
00:36:39,597 --> 00:36:41,299
I'm not worried.
David, listen to me.

663
00:36:41,332 --> 00:36:43,834
Listen to mommy.
Hold on to the horsie.
Hold on tight.

664
00:36:43,868 --> 00:36:47,338
I'll be right there with him,
I'll hold him. Now, come on.
[LAUGHS]

665
00:36:47,371 --> 00:36:49,674
Hold his arm. Hold his arm.
Hold his hand.

666
00:36:51,909 --> 00:36:53,544
Like this horse, David?

667
00:36:53,578 --> 00:36:54,946
MAN: There you go.

668
00:36:54,979 --> 00:36:57,648
[LAUGHING]
Here. Come on let's
get up on here.

669
00:36:58,683 --> 00:36:59,784
That's it.

670
00:36:59,817 --> 00:37:01,752
You have to put him on there.

671
00:37:01,786 --> 00:37:03,721
He can't just...
He doesn't get,
get on.

672
00:37:04,622 --> 00:37:05,823
Up!

673
00:37:05,856 --> 00:37:07,325
I got him.

674
00:37:07,858 --> 00:37:09,327
[GRUNTING]

675
00:37:12,563 --> 00:37:14,298
Okay, seat belt.
[LAUGHING]

676
00:37:17,735 --> 00:37:21,539
David? David. Hold on
to the pole, David.
Hold onto the pole.

677
00:37:21,572 --> 00:37:22,907
Put your hand on there
for your mother.

678
00:37:22,940 --> 00:37:24,375
[LAUGHING]

679
00:37:26,377 --> 00:37:27,612
Okay.

680
00:37:28,479 --> 00:37:29,747
Here we go.

681
00:37:30,514 --> 00:37:31,816
Hold on tight, David.

682
00:37:36,621 --> 00:37:38,689
[LAUGHING]
Great.

683
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:44,929
Careful with this pole now.

684
00:37:58,743 --> 00:37:59,777
[YELPS EXCITEDLY]

685
00:37:59,810 --> 00:38:00,978
There's your mother.

686
00:38:04,582 --> 00:38:05,816
[DAVID LAUGHING]

687
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:11,989
Hi, David. Hi, David.

688
00:38:12,023 --> 00:38:13,791
[LAUGHING] David.

689
00:38:30,608 --> 00:38:32,076
JOHN:
You worry too much
about him.

690
00:38:32,910 --> 00:38:34,378
SALLY: I get scared.

691
00:38:35,012 --> 00:38:36,080
He wasn't scared.

692
00:38:36,113 --> 00:38:38,482
This once he wasn't scared.

693
00:38:38,516 --> 00:38:40,151
Maybe you're the one
who gets scared.

694
00:38:40,184 --> 00:38:43,054
Oh, boy, you are just determined
to get me mad, aren't you?

695
00:38:43,988 --> 00:38:45,089
Man.

696
00:38:45,623 --> 00:38:46,857
I'm sorry.

697
00:38:46,891 --> 00:38:49,060
It was two minutes
and already
you're an expert.

698
00:38:49,093 --> 00:38:51,028
God bless men,
they're so smart.

699
00:38:53,764 --> 00:38:55,766
Sorry.
It wasn't called for.

700
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:57,034
Maybe it was called for.

701
00:38:57,635 --> 00:38:59,403
Yeah, it was.

702
00:38:59,437 --> 00:39:02,173
But let me apologize anyway.
I'm working on becoming
a nicer person.

703
00:39:02,206 --> 00:39:03,974
You're nice enough.
[GRUNTING]

704
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:06,010
Where have you been?
A mental home?

705
00:39:06,043 --> 00:39:09,180
You are a, what's the word,
volatile.
[SCOFFS]

706
00:39:09,213 --> 00:39:10,781
It's exciting.

707
00:39:10,815 --> 00:39:15,119
All right. Listen, I got
a pot roast on at home.

708
00:39:15,152 --> 00:39:18,089
If the apartment
isn't burnt down.
You like pot roast?

709
00:39:18,889 --> 00:39:20,091
I can't today.

710
00:39:20,725 --> 00:39:21,792
Okay.

711
00:39:21,826 --> 00:39:23,961
I'm supposed to be
at the store now.

712
00:39:23,994 --> 00:39:25,563
We're doing inventory.

713
00:39:25,596 --> 00:39:27,832
You don't need to make excuses.
We got to get home anyway.

714
00:39:27,865 --> 00:39:29,867
Thanks for
a great afternoon.
I'll call you.

715
00:39:29,900 --> 00:39:30,968
Sure.

716
00:39:31,001 --> 00:39:32,169
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

717
00:39:32,203 --> 00:39:33,571
Bye, David.

718
00:39:34,004 --> 00:39:35,406
David says bye.

719
00:39:44,715 --> 00:39:46,183
No, you're not.
Yes, I am.

720
00:39:46,217 --> 00:39:48,052
I said no!

721
00:39:48,085 --> 00:39:50,588
Well, I said yes.
Brenda, do you want to lose
your phone privileges?

722
00:39:50,621 --> 00:39:52,656
Mom, I am going!
Yes, yes, yes. Come in, now!

723
00:39:52,690 --> 00:39:54,859
Mom, I am going
whether you like it or not.

724
00:39:54,892 --> 00:39:56,527
You're gonna be sorry,
young lady.

725
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:58,829
Mom!
Brenda!

726
00:39:58,863 --> 00:40:00,731
SALLY:
Susan?
SUSAN:What?

727
00:40:00,765 --> 00:40:02,600
SALLY: Put the clothes back.
No.

728
00:40:02,633 --> 00:40:05,169
SALLY: Put the clothes back.
You're not going anywhere.

729
00:40:05,202 --> 00:40:06,971
Why?
"Why"?

730
00:40:07,004 --> 00:40:09,006
Look, this is your mother
you're talking to.

731
00:40:09,039 --> 00:40:10,241
I am not a moron.

732
00:40:10,274 --> 00:40:11,675
I know what kind of girl
Sandra is,

733
00:40:11,709 --> 00:40:14,912
and you are not spending
the night over at her house
without her parents.

734
00:40:14,945 --> 00:40:16,180
Nothing's gonna
happen to me.

735
00:40:16,213 --> 00:40:18,015
You're right. Because
you're not going.

736
00:40:18,048 --> 00:40:19,784
Ma, that's so unfair.

737
00:40:19,817 --> 00:40:21,752
Uh, and what am I supposed
to do here?

738
00:40:21,786 --> 00:40:23,788
I don't know.
Why don't you do
what you always do?

739
00:40:23,821 --> 00:40:25,623
Watch you take care of David?
It's all you ever do.

740
00:40:25,656 --> 00:40:26,957
Do we have to
do this again?

741
00:40:26,991 --> 00:40:30,127
David cannot take care
of himself and you can
take care of yourself.

742
00:40:30,161 --> 00:40:32,530
Then let me
take care of myself.
Let me go.

743
00:40:32,563 --> 00:40:34,031
Look, do we have to have
this fight?

744
00:40:34,064 --> 00:40:35,966
I don't want to have one.
Come on, I'll owe you one.

