01:06:49,872 --> 01:06:51,640
Just let me
take a walk, huh?

1230
01:06:51,674 --> 01:06:55,378
I'll regret anything I say now,
and so will you, I promise you.

1231
01:06:55,411 --> 01:06:57,413
SALLY:
So what is that, a threat?

1232
01:06:57,446 --> 01:07:01,484
No, it's an observation,
based on a 100 fights
and a thousand regrets.

1233
01:07:02,351 --> 01:07:03,552
Don't go.

1234
01:07:03,586 --> 01:07:05,521
It's better if I do.

1235
01:07:05,554 --> 01:07:07,390
I don't want to say anything
to hurt you.

1236
01:07:07,423 --> 01:07:10,126
Do you have something to say?
Go ahead and say it. Go ahead.

1237
01:07:10,159 --> 01:07:12,161
Come on, haven't you heard,
I have thick skin.

1238
01:07:12,194 --> 01:07:14,430
It was very hard for me

1239
01:07:14,463 --> 01:07:18,434
to put my wife in one part
of my heart so I could let you
into another.

1240
01:07:18,467 --> 01:07:20,770
I don't think you'll ever
do that with David.

1241
01:07:20,803 --> 01:07:22,671
Well, there's one
big difference here,

1242
01:07:22,705 --> 01:07:25,141
David is not dead.

1243
01:07:25,174 --> 01:07:26,675
No matter what
some people wish.

1244
01:07:26,709 --> 01:07:29,445
What, are you crazy?
I don't wish him dead,
I'm his father.

1245
01:07:29,478 --> 01:07:30,813
I love him.
Yeah.

1246
01:07:30,846 --> 01:07:32,181
From afar.

1247
01:07:32,214 --> 01:07:33,382
That is love.

1248
01:07:33,416 --> 01:07:36,485
What you do, breathing in air
as it comes out of his lungs,

1249
01:07:36,519 --> 01:07:38,454
it's lunacy.
It's not good for him.

1250
01:07:38,487 --> 01:07:41,323
I think I know a little better
than you what's good for David.

1251
01:07:41,357 --> 01:07:42,825
Do you?

1252
01:07:42,858 --> 01:07:44,627
What the hell is that
supposed to mean?

1253
01:07:44,660 --> 01:07:47,730
It means, I have to beg you
to let me help your son.

1254
01:07:47,763 --> 01:07:48,697
You should thank me.

1255
01:07:48,731 --> 01:07:51,434
Working a VCR is not gonna
change his life.

1256
01:07:51,467 --> 01:07:53,269
Nothing is gonna change
his life.

1257
01:07:53,302 --> 01:07:54,870
You won't let it!

1258
01:07:54,904 --> 01:07:57,440
You're so sure you know
what he can do
and what he can't do,

1259
01:07:57,473 --> 01:07:58,741
you won't let him
do anything.

1260
01:07:58,774 --> 01:08:00,409
What do you
want from me?

1261
01:08:00,443 --> 01:08:01,844
I want a wife.

1262
01:08:01,877 --> 01:08:03,312
I don't want to be alone.

1263
01:08:03,345 --> 01:08:04,914
I don't want
David to be alone.

1264
01:08:04,947 --> 01:08:07,483
How can he be alone?
You wear him
like a second skin.

1265
01:08:07,516 --> 01:08:09,251
I am fighting for
my kid's life here.

1266
01:08:09,285 --> 01:08:11,420
I don't have time
for all these other feelings.

1267
01:08:11,454 --> 01:08:13,389
That's the second time
you've said that.

1268
01:08:13,422 --> 01:08:16,292
You're not fighting
for his life, you're fighting
to control his life.

1269
01:08:16,325 --> 01:08:18,627
You use him,
don't you see that?

1270
01:08:18,661 --> 01:08:21,230
I have sacrificed everything
for him.

1271
01:08:21,263 --> 01:08:24,233
You have sacrificed everyone
for him.

1272
01:08:27,236 --> 01:08:28,571
You said you wanted to leave.

1273
01:08:29,505 --> 01:08:30,673
So, leave.

1274
01:08:32,775 --> 01:08:34,710
[FOOTSTEPS FADING]

1275
01:08:47,690 --> 01:08:52,595
"As taut as a pulled trigger,
the shattering climax will
leave you gasping for more."

1276
01:08:52,628 --> 01:08:53,896
Yeah, right.

1277
01:08:54,864 --> 01:08:56,432
There we go.

1278
01:08:57,733 --> 01:09:00,736
"The joyous escape
of two Siamese cats,
and a bull dog

1279
01:09:00,769 --> 01:09:05,241
"turn a provincial mining
town upside down. A mirthful.
G-rated movie. 110 minutes."

1280
01:09:05,274 --> 01:09:07,543
What do you say, David,
you ready for a little mirth?

1281
01:09:09,245 --> 01:09:10,479
David?

1282
01:09:10,513 --> 01:09:12,481
[GUN FIRING]

1283
01:09:12,515 --> 01:09:14,316
[DAVID LAUGHING]

1284
01:09:15,017 --> 01:09:16,852
[HORN TOOTING]

1285
01:09:16,886 --> 01:09:18,854
[DAVID LAUGHING]

1286
01:09:20,623 --> 01:09:22,525
NARRATOR:
The old Union Jack

1287
01:09:22,558 --> 01:09:24,927
still waves triumphantly
over the land.

1288
01:09:27,530 --> 01:09:30,833
[LAUGHING]
MAN:
Still stands the...

1289
01:09:30,866 --> 01:09:32,835
[INDISTINCT CHATTER FROM TV]

1290
01:09:46,515 --> 01:09:49,785
MAN:
Cutting across
main street on the left to
the railroad tracks.

1291
01:09:49,818 --> 01:09:52,488
Beyond the railroad tracks
is Polish town.

1292
01:09:52,521 --> 01:09:55,224
[INDISTINCT CHATTER
FROM TV CONTINUES]

1293
01:10:02,398 --> 01:10:03,766
[LAUGHING]

1294
01:10:05,668 --> 01:10:07,870
[CHANGES TAPE]

1295
01:10:29,992 --> 01:10:31,961
Oh! Hi, Sid.

1296
01:10:31,994 --> 01:10:33,562
Is my sister in?

1297
01:10:33,596 --> 01:10:34,964
Uh, she's in there.

1298
01:10:36,432 --> 01:10:37,533
She's in there?

1299
01:10:37,967 --> 01:10:39,268
Right.

1300
01:10:42,805 --> 01:10:44,306
[DAVID LAUGHING]

1301
01:10:45,474 --> 01:10:47,676
What are you doing in here?

1302
01:10:47,710 --> 01:10:49,878
SALLY: Just waiting
for the rain to stop.

1303
01:10:49,912 --> 01:10:52,047
I've been trying to reach you
for over two days.

1304
01:10:52,081 --> 01:10:54,683
So has John. The next time
you to go into hiding

1305
01:10:54,717 --> 01:10:56,719
would you please switch on
the answering machine?

1306
01:10:56,752 --> 01:10:58,787
What's the matter with you?
You look like hell.

1307
01:10:58,821 --> 01:11:01,357
I spend my time sleeping
a lot lately.

1308
01:11:01,390 --> 01:11:02,791
What's the matter?
You two
have a fight?

1309
01:11:02,825 --> 01:11:04,593
Big deal, couples fight.

1310
01:11:05,628 --> 01:11:07,930
Oh, honey.
Bea.

1311
01:11:07,963 --> 01:11:10,332
What? What?
Will you tell me
something?

1312
01:11:10,366 --> 01:11:12,668
Am I a bad person?
What do you mean?
You're the best.

1313
01:11:12,701 --> 01:11:14,870
No, come on, just give me
the truth, okay.

1314
01:11:14,903 --> 01:11:16,405
[SIGHS] All right.

1315
01:11:17,940 --> 01:11:19,742
What happened?

1316
01:11:19,775 --> 01:11:21,744
David can work the VCR.

1317
01:11:22,811 --> 01:11:24,313
What?

1318
01:11:24,346 --> 01:11:27,616
In a million years, would you
ever have believed that David
could work a VCR?

1319
01:11:28,550 --> 01:11:30,352
I guess not.

1320
01:11:30,386 --> 01:11:31,854
[SCOFFS]
I had that damn machine

1321
01:11:31,887 --> 01:11:34,423
in the house for three years
and he never touched it.

1322
01:11:34,456 --> 01:11:37,426
Two weeks with John
and he's an expert.

1323
01:11:37,459 --> 01:11:40,462
Do you remember how long
it took you
to teach me how to use it?

1324
01:11:40,496 --> 01:11:43,732
How are we discussing how smart
David is or how dumb you are?

1325
01:11:44,600 --> 01:11:45,868
[DAVID GRUNTING]

1326
01:11:47,870 --> 01:11:49,872
John said that I don't let him
do anything.

1327
01:11:50,706 --> 01:11:52,408
I think he's right.

1328
01:11:52,441 --> 01:11:54,677
I mean,
if he can work a VCR...

1329
01:11:54,710 --> 01:11:57,813
I mean, who knows what else
he can do, what he can be.

1330
01:11:57,846 --> 01:11:59,148
What he can be?

1331
01:11:59,181 --> 01:12:01,617
Honey, David is
what he can be.

1332
01:12:01,650 --> 01:12:02,985
He's impaired.

1333
01:12:03,018 --> 01:12:04,953
That's just a word.

1334
01:12:04,987 --> 01:12:07,089
Am I the one who said
what it meant?

1335
01:12:07,122 --> 01:12:09,692
I mean, did I make him
like this?

1336
01:12:09,725 --> 01:12:11,527
Stop that. You're not
that important.

1337
01:12:11,560 --> 01:12:12,861
God made him this way.

1338
01:12:12,895 --> 01:12:14,463
Well, Bea, maybe there's
two gods.

1339
01:12:14,496 --> 01:12:17,966
The one that cooked his brains,
the one that made sure
they stayed that way.

1340
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:20,069
What do you think you did
that was so terrible?

1341
01:12:20,102 --> 01:12:22,171
You had an afflicted child.

1342
01:12:22,204 --> 01:12:25,107
You took care of him.
That's all. Nobody could have
been a more devoted mother.

1343
01:12:25,140 --> 01:12:26,575
Yeah, well...

1344
01:12:26,608 --> 01:12:28,977
[SCOFFS] I mean, Susan would
agree with that.

1345
01:12:29,011 --> 01:12:31,680
Do you think
she thinks she had
a devoted mother?

1346
01:12:31,714 --> 01:12:33,682
And how about Phil?

1347
01:12:33,716 --> 01:12:36,518
You did the best you could.
That's all anybody can do.

1348
01:12:37,853 --> 01:12:39,788
How good was my best?

1349
01:12:39,822 --> 01:12:43,525
David, come on, honey,
you want...
You want to go upstairs?

1350
01:12:43,559 --> 01:12:45,094
Let's go up, come on,
stand up.

1351
01:12:46,929 --> 01:12:48,163
[GRUNTS]

1352
01:12:51,967 --> 01:12:53,969
I'm gonna zap something
for lunch.

1353
01:12:54,002 --> 01:12:55,504
Weren't you radio active?

1354
01:12:55,537 --> 01:12:56,739
Please.

1355
01:12:56,772 --> 01:12:59,141
SALLY: Good. That'll
leave more for us.

1356
01:13:01,543 --> 01:13:02,845
[GRUNTING]

1357
01:13:26,268 --> 01:13:28,971
Just this once
don't be hard on yourself.

1358
01:13:29,004 --> 01:13:33,008
You know, doesn't make you that
important just because your
punishment's always the worst.

1359
01:13:37,846 --> 01:13:40,849
Now, don't worry,
John will fix everything.

1360
01:13:40,883 --> 01:13:43,786
Yeah? And how is he gonna
do that?

1361
01:13:43,819 --> 01:13:45,521
Well, when you two are...

1362
01:13:47,055 --> 01:13:48,724
When we two what?

1363
01:13:49,124 --> 01:13:50,726
You know...

1364
01:13:50,759 --> 01:13:53,028
You... Ugh, Bea,

1365
01:13:53,061 --> 01:13:54,997
don't dye your shoes yet.

1366
01:13:55,030 --> 01:13:57,099
Now, what does that mean?

1367
01:13:57,132 --> 01:13:59,168
It means I don't know
if I'm interested.

1368
01:13:59,201 --> 01:14:01,170
Of course you're interested,
you like him.

1369
01:14:01,203 --> 01:14:03,172
Yeah, but what if
I don't love him?

1370
01:14:03,205 --> 01:14:05,474
Love him? Who expected you
to love him?

1371
01:14:07,109 --> 01:14:08,177
Didn't you?

1372
01:14:08,844 --> 01:14:10,779
Of course not.

1373
01:14:10,813 --> 01:14:12,548
I was hoping
for companionship.

1374
01:14:12,581 --> 01:14:14,917
Sally, he's a very rich man.

1375
01:14:14,950 --> 01:14:16,752
He can take you out
of this crummy life.

1376
01:14:18,153 --> 01:14:20,189
You can get someone
to take care of David.

1377
01:14:20,222 --> 01:14:22,658
You can...
Vacations in Europe.

1378
01:14:22,691 --> 01:14:25,194
You can walk the aisle
of Bloomingdales like
a normal person.

1379
01:14:26,795 --> 01:14:28,163
Did you hear
what you just said?

1380
01:14:28,197 --> 01:14:29,998
I don't care
what I just said.

1381
01:14:31,834 --> 01:14:34,169
There's nothing
he wouldn't give you.

1382
01:14:34,203 --> 01:14:36,004
Well, then why marry him?

1383
01:14:36,038 --> 01:14:38,207
Why don't I just
forge his name
on a check?

1384
01:14:38,240 --> 01:14:41,743
Why don't you just
stop making jokes
and ruining your life?

1385
01:14:41,777 --> 01:14:44,947
Uh, I don't believe what
I'm hearing here.

1386
01:14:44,980 --> 01:14:46,882
Did you love Stephen
when you married him?

1387
01:14:46,915 --> 01:14:48,684
Oh, love?
That's absolutely irrelevant.

1388
01:14:48,717 --> 01:14:51,119
I was 24-years-old,
I was entitled to be in love.

1389
01:14:51,153 --> 01:14:52,254
And I'm not?

1390
01:14:53,589 --> 01:14:55,891
Well, when did
that happen, Bea?

1391
01:14:55,924 --> 01:14:59,094
When David was born?
When David turned out
the way he turned out,

1392
01:14:59,127 --> 01:15:01,997
did that make me [STAMMERS]
unworthy of love?

1393
01:15:02,030 --> 01:15:03,232
That's not what I'm saying.

1394
01:15:03,265 --> 01:15:05,033
God!

1395
01:15:05,067 --> 01:15:07,736
What are you saying, then?
No matter what harm I've done
anyone else,

1396
01:15:07,769 --> 01:15:09,671
I've done more to myself.

1397
01:15:10,706 --> 01:15:12,241
I'm not gonna settle.

1398
01:15:12,274 --> 01:15:15,110
I wouldn't degrade myself
any further
than I already have.

1399
01:15:15,143 --> 01:15:16,245
I won't settle.

1400
01:15:16,278 --> 01:15:17,846
I'm not asking
you to settle.

1401
01:15:17,880 --> 01:15:19,815
Yes, you are.
Of course you are.

1402
01:15:19,848 --> 01:15:21,650
I'm asking you
to save yourself.

1403
01:15:21,683 --> 01:15:23,685
No you're not!
You're demanding it.

1404
01:15:23,919 --> 01:15:25,153
Why?

1405
01:15:25,187 --> 01:15:27,589
Because I'm exhausted from
worrying about you.

1406
01:15:29,091 --> 01:15:30,959
I haven't got the energy
to do it anymore.

1407
01:15:31,960 --> 01:15:33,595
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1408
01:15:34,696 --> 01:15:36,265
Well, then don't
do it anymore.

1409
01:15:37,966 --> 01:15:39,167
Don't do it.

1410
01:15:40,068 --> 01:15:41,270
I never asked you to.

1411
01:15:42,404 --> 01:15:44,039
I never wanted you to.

1412
01:16:02,090 --> 01:16:03,859
Tell me something.

1413
01:16:03,892 --> 01:16:07,195
Why is it that
the people who don't
screw up their lives

1414
01:16:07,229 --> 01:16:09,064
always feel guilty
about people who do?

1415
01:16:12,334 --> 01:16:13,735
I don't know.

1416
01:16:16,238 --> 01:16:17,372
Hug me.

1417
01:16:21,710 --> 01:16:22,878
[SNIFFLES]

1418
01:16:24,046 --> 01:16:25,280
I resent you.

1419
01:16:25,314 --> 01:16:28,183
I know that.
I got the gifts to prove it.

1420
01:16:28,216 --> 01:16:30,052
Sometimes I hate you.

1421
01:16:30,085 --> 01:16:31,253
And I love you.

1422
01:16:34,222 --> 01:16:36,258
Ours is not a simple
relationship.

1423
01:16:36,291 --> 01:16:39,294
Well, who says
simple is good?

1424
01:16:39,328 --> 01:16:42,764
[SNIFFS] You know all the parts
I meant and the parts I didn't.

1425
01:16:46,168 --> 01:16:47,336
[DOOR CLOSES]

1426
01:16:55,143 --> 01:16:56,878
It's back ordered.

1427
01:16:56,912 --> 01:16:59,081
Four, maybe five weeks.

1428
01:16:59,114 --> 01:17:02,150
What can I say, I sell it,
I don't manufacture it.

1429
01:17:02,184 --> 01:17:04,086
Uh, excuse me, sir.

1430
01:17:04,119 --> 01:17:06,788
The wallpaper you sold us
has peeled off the walls and

1431
01:17:06,822 --> 01:17:08,957
is lying in my
dining room floor.

1432
01:17:08,991 --> 01:17:10,158
What are you doing here?

1433
01:17:11,226 --> 01:17:12,861
She's kidding.

1434
01:17:12,894 --> 01:17:13,996
I'm not kidding.

1435
01:17:14,029 --> 01:17:16,698
Please come in the back before
you wreck my business.

1436
01:17:16,732 --> 01:17:18,900
Excuse me.

1437
01:17:18,934 --> 01:17:21,203
Come on, honey.
I am not kidding.

1438
01:17:21,236 --> 01:17:22,871
Oh, here they are.

1439
01:17:22,904 --> 01:17:25,273
Put this in you hand. come on.
Come on.
[GRUNTING]

1440
01:17:26,341 --> 01:17:27,843
David.

1441
01:17:27,876 --> 01:17:29,778
I want you to sit down
here, okay?

1442
01:17:29,811 --> 01:17:30,879
Here.

1443
01:17:31,113 --> 01:17:32,381
Sit.

1444
01:17:32,414 --> 01:17:34,349
Play solitaire, okay?
[GRUNTS]

1445
01:17:34,383 --> 01:17:36,218
Stay there and don't move.

1446
01:17:36,251 --> 01:17:37,953
JOHN: I'm surprised to see you.

1447
01:17:37,986 --> 01:17:40,422
Oh... [SIGHS]

1448
01:17:40,455 --> 01:17:43,025
We just left Bea running
amok in Bloomingdale.

1449
01:17:43,058 --> 01:17:44,726
[GRUNTING]

1450
01:17:44,760 --> 01:17:47,095
I'm glad you're here,
gives me a chance
to apologize.

1451
01:17:47,129 --> 01:17:48,430
For what?

1452
01:17:48,463 --> 01:17:50,832
Everything you said was true.
I should thank you.

1453
01:17:52,200 --> 01:17:53,368
You can thank me tonight.

1454
01:17:54,302 --> 01:17:55,470
I can't.

1455
01:17:55,504 --> 01:17:56,738
Tomorrow night?

1456
01:17:59,307 --> 01:18:00,842
You're such a nice man.

1457
01:18:01,910 --> 01:18:03,178
You really helped my kid.

1458
01:18:04,913 --> 01:18:06,748
You really helped me
and I owe you.

1459
01:18:08,083 --> 01:18:09,418
JOHN:
You can pay for dinner.

1460
01:18:11,853 --> 01:18:13,889
I owe you too much
to keep seeing you.

1461
01:18:17,959 --> 01:18:19,394
That I don't understand.

1462
01:18:20,328 --> 01:18:21,496
Sure you do.

1463
01:18:23,098 --> 01:18:25,400
You don't have to...

1464
01:18:25,434 --> 01:18:28,303
love me to
keep on seeing me,
you know?

1465
01:18:28,336 --> 01:18:30,772
[CHUCKLES] Yeah, I do.

1466
01:18:30,806 --> 01:18:33,041
You're that kind of guy.

1467
01:18:33,075 --> 01:18:34,910
Besides, before you know it,
the mistake,

1468
01:18:34,943 --> 01:18:37,913
the relief of being with anybody
with real feelings for me.

1469
01:18:38,413 --> 01:18:40,415
Then I will hurt you.

1470
01:18:43,251 --> 01:18:45,120
You might learn
to feel something for me.

1471
01:18:46,121 --> 01:18:47,322
Miracles happen.

